@mikayelh Unfortunately yes, see below. In a nutshell, after `pip install langchain[all]` it is enough to `import langchain` and _all uncaught_(?) subsequent exceptions will trigger `HumbugReport.publish()` 

Langchain attempts to import all supported vectorstores, [including deeplake](https://github.com/hwchase17/langchain/blob/e5611565b7436a522cf700c8b1125a56f17bc900/langchain/vectorstores/__init__.py#L16). If it is installed, it will [import deeplake](https://github.com/hwchase17/langchain/blob/e5611565b7436a522cf700c8b1125a56f17bc900/langchain/vectorstores/deeplake.py#L10).

upon `import deeplake`, a HumbugReporter is set up and an [exception hook added](https://github.com/activeloopai/deeplake/blob/5146a333092b7f19e14469d4ad4b208e4e693c6d/deeplake/__init__.py#L89). That is any future exception triggers a `reporter.publish()` call to https://spire.bugout.dev.

